<section xml:id="C7.S7">
<title>Integral Representations</title>        
 
<subsection xml:id="C7.S7.SS1">
<title>Error Functions and Dawson’s Integral</title>           
<para xml:id="C7.S7.SS1.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="1" xml:id="C7.S7.SS1.p1.s1">
Integrals of the type <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C7.S7.SS1.p1.m1">\int e^{-z^{2}}R(z)\mathrm{d}z</Math> , where <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C7.S7.SS1.p1.m2">R(z)</Math> is an arbitrary rational function, can be written in closed form in terms of the error functions and elementary functions.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="2" xml:id="C7.S7.SS1.p1.s2">
<Math equation-number="7.7.1" mode="display" xml:id="C7.S7.E1">\operatorname{erfc}z=\frac{2}{\pi}e^{-z^{2}}\int_{0}^{\infty}\frac{e^{-z^{2}t^ {2}}}{t^{2}+1}\mathrm{d}t, if |\operatorname{ph}z|\leq\frac{1}{4}\pi,</Math> <Math equation-number="7.7.2" mode="display" xml:id="C7.S7.E2">w\left(z\right)=\frac{1}{\pi i}\int_{-\infty}^{\infty}\frac{e^{-t^{2}}\mathrm{ d}t}{t-z}=\frac{2z}{\pi i}\int_{0}^{\infty}\frac{e^{-t^{2}}\mathrm{d}t}{t^{2}- z^{2}}, if \Im z&gt;0</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="3" xml:id="C7.S7.SS1.p1.s3">
<Math equation-number="7.7.3" mode="display" xml:id="C7.S7.E3">\int_{0}^{\infty}e^{-at^{2}+2izt}\mathrm{d}t=\frac{1}{2}\sqrt{\frac{\pi}{a}}e^ {-z^{2}/a}+\frac{i}{\sqrt{a}}F\left(\frac{z}{\sqrt{a}}\right), if \Re a&gt;0</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="4" sentence-num-in-section="4" xml:id="C7.S7.SS1.p1.s4">
<Math equation-number="7.7.4" mode="display" xml:id="C7.S7.E4">\int_{0}^{\infty}\frac{e^{-at}}{\sqrt{t+z^{2}}}\mathrm{d}t=\sqrt{\frac{\pi}{a} }e^{az^{2}}\operatorname{erfc}\left(\sqrt{a}z\right), if \Re a&gt;0, \Re z&gt;0</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="5" sentence-num-in-section="5" xml:id="C7.S7.SS1.p1.s5">
<Math equation-number="7.7.5" mode="display" xml:id="C7.S7.E5">\int_{0}^{1}\frac{e^{-at^{2}}}{t^{2}+1}\mathrm{d}t=\frac{\pi}{4}e^{a}\left(1-( \operatorname{erf}\sqrt{a})^{2}\right), if \Re a&gt;0</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="6" sentence-num-in-section="6" xml:id="C7.S7.SS1.p1.s6">
<Math equation-number="7.7.6" mode="display" xml:id="C7.S7.E6">\int_{x}^{\infty}e^{-(at^{2}+2bt+c)}\mathrm{d}t=\frac{1}{2}\sqrt{\frac{\pi}{a} }e^{(b^{2}-ac)/a}\operatorname{erfc}\left(\sqrt{a}x+\frac{b}{\sqrt{a}}\right), if \Re a&gt;0</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="7" sentence-num-in-section="7" xml:id="C7.S7.SS1.p1.s7">
<Math equation-number="7.7.7" mode="display" xml:id="C7.S7.E7">\int_{x}^{\infty}e^{-a^{2}t^{2}-(b^{2}/t^{2})}\mathrm{d}t=\frac{\sqrt{\pi}}{4a }\left(e^{2ab}\operatorname{erfc}\left(ax+(b/x)\right)+e^{-2ab}\operatorname{ erfc}\left(ax-(b/x)\right)\right), if x&gt;0, |\operatorname{ph}a|&lt;\tfrac{1}{4}\pi</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="8" sentence-num-in-section="8" xml:id="C7.S7.SS1.p1.s8">
<Math equation-number="7.7.8" mode="display" xml:id="C7.S7.E8">\int_{0}^{\infty}e^{-a^{2}t^{2}-(b^{2}/t^{2})}\mathrm{d}t=\frac{\sqrt{\pi}}{2a }e^{-2ab}, if |\operatorname{ph}a|&lt;\tfrac{1}{4}\pi, |\operatorname{ph}b|&lt;\tfrac{1}{4}\pi</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="9" sentence-num-in-section="9" xml:id="C7.S7.SS1.p1.s9">
<Math equation-number="7.7.9" mode="display" xml:id="C7.S7.E9">\int_{0}^{x}\operatorname{erf}t\mathrm{d}t=x\operatorname{erf}x+\frac{1}{\sqrt {\pi}}\left(e^{-x^{2}}-1\right)</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C7.S7.SS2">
<title>Auxiliary Functions</title>         
 
<para xml:id="C7.S7.SS2.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="10" xml:id="C7.S7.SS2.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="7.7.10" mode="display" xml:id="C7.S7.E10">\mathrm{f}\left(z\right)=\frac{1}{\pi\sqrt{2}}\int_{0}^{\infty}\frac{e^{-\pi z ^{2}t/2}}{\sqrt{t}(t^{2}+1)}\mathrm{d}t, if |\operatorname{ph}z|\leq\frac{1}{4}\pi,</Math> , <Math equation-number="7.7.11" mode="display" xml:id="C7.S7.E11">\mathrm{g}\left(z\right)=\frac{1}{\pi\sqrt{2}}\int_{0}^{\infty}\frac{\sqrt{t}e ^{-\pi z^{2}t/2}}{t^{2}+1}\mathrm{d}t, if |\operatorname{ph}z|\leq\frac{1}{4}\pi,</Math> <Math equation-number="7.7.12" mode="display" xml:id="C7.S7.E12">\mathrm{g}\left(z\right)+i\mathrm{f}\left(z\right)=e^{-\pi iz^{2}/2}\int_{z}^{ \infty}e^{\pi it^{2}/2}\mathrm{d}t</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
<paragraph xml:id="C7.S7.Px1">
<title>Mellin–Barnes Integrals</title>    
<para xml:id="C7.S7.Px1.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="11" xml:id="C7.S7.Px1.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="7.7.13" mode="display" xml:id="C7.S7.E13">\mathrm{f}\left(z\right)=\frac{(2\pi)^{-3/2}}{2\pi i}\int_{c-i\infty}^{c+i \infty}\zeta^{-s}\Gamma\left(s\right)\Gamma\left(s+\tfrac{1}{2}\right)\*\Gamma \left(s+\tfrac{3}{4}\right)\Gamma\left(\tfrac{1}{4}-s\right)\mathrm{d}s,</Math> <Math equation-number="7.7.14" mode="display" xml:id="C7.S7.E14">\mathrm{g}\left(z\right)=\frac{(2\pi)^{-3/2}}{2\pi i}\int_{c-i\infty}^{c+i \infty}\zeta^{-s}\Gamma\left(s\right)\Gamma\left(s+\tfrac{1}{2}\right)\*\Gamma \left(s+\tfrac{1}{4}\right)\Gamma\left(\tfrac{3}{4}-s\right)\mathrm{d}s</Math>.
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="2" sentence-num-in-section="12" xml:id="C7.S7.Px1.p1.s2">
In (7.7.13) and (7.7.14) the integration paths are straight lines, <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C7.S7.Px1.p1.m1">\zeta=\frac{1}{16}\pi^{2}z^{4}</Math> , and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C7.S7.Px1.p1.m2">c</Math> is a constant such that <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C7.S7.Px1.p1.m3">0&lt;c&lt;\frac{1}{4}</Math> in (7.7.13), and <Math mode="inline" xml:id="C7.S7.Px1.p1.m4">0&lt;c&lt;\frac{3}{4}</Math> in (7.7.14).
</sentence>

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="3" sentence-num-in-section="13" xml:id="C7.S7.Px1.p1.s3">
<Math equation-number="7.7.15" mode="display" xml:id="C7.S7.E15">\int_{0}^{\infty}e^{-at}\cos\left(t^{2}\right)\mathrm{d}t=\sqrt{\frac{\pi}{2}} \mathrm{f}\left(\frac{a}{\sqrt{2\pi}}\right), if \Re a&gt;0,</Math> <Math equation-number="7.7.16" mode="display" xml:id="C7.S7.E16">\int_{0}^{\infty}e^{-at}\sin\left(t^{2}\right)\mathrm{d}t=\sqrt{\frac{\pi}{2}} \mathrm{g}\left(\frac{a}{\sqrt{2\pi}}\right), if \Re a&gt;0</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>

 
</paragraph>
 
</subsection>
 
